gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 127, Jazz 126
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets defeated the Jazz, 127-126, in overtime. Alperen Sengun recorded a career-high tying 37 points, along with 14 rebounds and six assists for the Rockets, while Jabari Smith Jr. added 24 points (4-8 3pt. FG) and 10 rebounds in the victory. Jordan Clarkson (33 points, season-high 12 rebounds) and Collin Sexton (28 points, five assists) combined for 61 points for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Rockets snap a 3-game losing streak as they improve to 20-21 on the season, while the Jazz fall to 22-22.
